etest.log
coverage.out
.idea/
*__debug*
.ref/
.DS_Store

# Go binaries — never commit compiled output.
# Matches the build targets from server/Dockerfile and benchmark/Dockerfile,
# plus any ad-hoc `go build` output in the repo root or subfolders.
#
# IMPORTANT: bare names like `benchmarkworker` would also match the
# directory `benchmark/cmd/benchmarkworker/` and silently hide every new
# .go file added inside it. Always use a path (with `/`) for binaries
# whose name collides with a package directory.
server/main
server/dex-server
# go test -c output (package-named executables, e.g. cluster.test).
*.test
benchmark/benchmarkworker
benchmark/cmd/benchmarkworker/benchmarkworker
benchmark/dex-benchmark-worker
/benchmarkworker
/dex-server
/dex-benchmark-worker

# Catch-all: Go binaries have no extension on Linux/macOS.
# Exclude common non-binary extensionless files via negation.
# If a new extensionless source file is added, add a negation here.
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
.idea/

# Secrets — never commit credentials or local env files.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
credentials.json
token.json